    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_intro_title">Drag the active piece and line up your launch</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_intro_body">The current piece starts in the launch dock. Drag it left or right under the board, release when the preview looks good, and it will drop into the nearest valid lane.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_systems_title">Use action blocks when the board gets crowded</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_systems_body">Hold swaps the current piece, Pause freezes the run, Block Properties explains symbols, and Settings changes the look. These buttons also follow your chosen board block style.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_specials_title">Special blocks can save tight boards</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_specials_body">Some pieces carry special effects. Learn what each icon does so you can clear a row, clear a column, slip through gaps, or punch through danger when the board gets crowded.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_ready_title">You are ready to launch in StackShift</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_ready_body">Keep your launches clean, plan for the next queue, and use specials before pressure builds too high. When you want a refresher, come back to this guide anytime.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_ready_tutorial_hint">Open Tutorial anytime to review launching, queue awareness, and special block effects.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_stackshift_ready_settings_hint">Open Settings to change the language, theme, colors, and block style before your next run.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_intro_title">Drag any of the three pieces onto the board</string>
    <string name="tutorial_intro_body">Three shapes wait in the tray. Pick the one you want, drag it onto any empty cells, and release to place it exactly where it fits.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_systems_title">Think about the whole tray, not just one move</string>
    <string name="tutorial_systems_body">After placing one piece, the remaining tray stays on screen. When all three are used, a fresh trio appears. Try to leave enough space for every shape you still have.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_specials_title">Rows and columns clear with full coverage</string>
    <string name="tutorial_specials_body">There are no special pieces here. Instead, fill an entire row or an entire column to clear it. If both complete together, they clear at the same time.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ready_title">You are ready for the new block puzzle flow</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ready_body">Keep scanning the tray, set up row and column clears, and avoid trapping large shapes. When none of the three pieces fit anymore, the run ends.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ready_block_properties_hint">Open Tutorial whenever you want to revisit free placement and simultaneous row/column clears.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ready_tutorial_hint">Open Tutorial whenever you want to revisit free placement and simultaneous row/column clears.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_ready_settings_hint">Open Settings to change the language, theme, colors, and block style before your next run.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_mergeshift_intro_title">Launch pieces to merge same-valued blocks</string>
    <string name="tutorial_mergeshift_intro_body">In MergeShift, pieces are launched from the dock. When a block lands on another with the same value, they merge into a higher value. Keep merging to clear space and reach higher scores.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_mergeshift_systems_title">Plan your mergers to prevent overflow</string>
    <string name="tutorial_mergeshift_systems_body">Every piece you launch adds to the column height. If any column reaches the top, the game ends. Use the preview to see where your piece will land and which blocks it might merge with.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_mergeshift_specials_title">Combine multiple merges for bigger combos</string>
    <string name="tutorial_mergeshift_specials_body">A single launch can trigger a chain reaction of merges. These combos award more points and clear more space on the board, helping you stay in the game longer.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_mergeshift_ready_title">You are ready for MergeShift</string>
    <string name="tutorial_mergeshift_ready_body">Focus on keeping your columns low and setting up high-value merges. Good luck reaching the highest numbers!</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_step_counter">Guide %1$d / %2$d</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_drag_title">Drag a tray piece onto the board</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_drag_body">Touch one of the three shapes in the tray, move it over the board, and line it up with the highlighted cells.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_drag_to_board">Drag the highlighted tray piece into the glowing target area.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_drag_ready">Nice — release now. Once it snaps into the highlighted cells, the next guide will open automatically.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_aim_hint">Drop the piece inside the highlighted cells to continue.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_target_locked">Perfect — keep it there and release to continue.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_waiting">Placement accepted. Preparing the next guided moment…</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_line_clear_title">Complete a row to clear it</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_line_clear_body">Place this shape into the guided spot so the row becomes full, flashes, and disappears.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_column_clearer_title">Complete a column to clear it</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_column_clearer_body">Now use the highlighted placement to finish a full column and open vertical space.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_row_clearer_title">Rows open horizontal space</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_row_clearer_body">A full row clears instantly. Aim for the highlighted cells and watch the board open across the width.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_ghost_title">The tray matters as much as the board</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_ghost_body">Before you place a shape, glance at the other two pieces. Good runs come from leaving room for the whole tray, not just the current move.</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_heavy_title">Clear both directions together</string>
    <string name="interactive_onboarding_heavy_body">Some placements finish a row and a column at the same time. Use the guided spot to trigger a bigger double clear.</string>
</resources>

